claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
operating a Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO)-capable subscriber node in a wireless communication network;
measuring a received transmission to determine channel conditions; and
upon receiving a transmission wherein said channel conditions meet specified conditions,
switching between said non-MIMO mode and said MIMO mode;
wherein said specified conditions comprise a cross-polarization discrimination between two spatial subchannels or an error vector magnitude.

5. The method of claim 1 further comprising:
communicating data with the access point in a MIMO period if said subscriber node is in said MIMO mode;
communicating data with said access point in a non-MIMO period if said subscriber node is in said non-MIMO mode.
